title: [ IOTDB-116]Performance statistics module
body: In order to better grasp the performance of database in practical application, we add a module to count the time-consuming of each operation. This module can statistic the avg time-consuming of each operation and the proportion of each operation fall into a time range.A output example is in below. This module uses asynchronous operation to reduce the impact on the normal speed of the database.The queue size is controlled by a param in iotdb-engine.properties, which is 'performance_stat_memory_in_kb'. The output is in log_measure.log file. **configuration parameter** locationconf/iotdb-engine.properties item // Is stat performance of sub-module enable enable_performance_stat=false // The interval of display statistic result in ms. performance_stat_display_interval=60000 // The memory used for performance_stat in kb. performance_stat_memory_in_kb=20

title: [IOTDB-105] fix bug of write lock operation in merge() when IoTDB recover
body:
Currenttly, when IoTDB revover, it is possible that exception of write lock operation will be thrown as shown below.
![](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16442316/58675775-6b453780-8388-11e9-847c-a49cf6b15384.png)
After checking, during the MERGE of recovery, locking and unlocking operations are not in pairs. This is mainly because FileNodeProcessor.merge() contains 2 locking operations and 3 unlocking operations. In normal process, an extra locking operation is processed before merge(). Therefore, to fix this bug, the locking operation is moved into merge().

title: Refactor iotdb code for cluster
body:
This pr contains all modifications of iotdb and tsfile module for cluster module, mainly contains the following features:
1.  Implement interface `Serializable` for all Physical plans. Because physical plans need to be transmitted over the network in cluster modules.
2. Add method `clone()` for all `Expression` and `Filter`Because  in distributed query process, each query node needs to prune on the original filter tree and construct a new filter tree. So it is necessary to clone the original filter condition.
3. Abstract a layer of interface `IQueryProcessExecutor ` from `QueryProcessExecutor` for distributed implementation.
4. Add some metadata method in metadata module which has no conflicts with the current code for cluster module.

title: Fix a clerical error in console display when run 'start-server.sh'
body:
When I run `incubator-iotdb/iotdb/iotdb/bin/start-server.sh` on Unix/OS X, the output in console is

```bash
---------------------
Starting IoTDB
---------------------
Maximum memory allocation pool = 4096MMB, initial memory allocation pool = 800MMB
...
```

You can see that there are redundant "M"s in " `4096MMB`"  and "`800MMB`". I have just removed them.

The problem comes from the duplicate declaration of "M" in line 78 & 149 of file `incubator-iotdb/iotdb/iotdb/conf/iotdb-env.sh`:

- Line 78

```bash
MAX_HEAP_SIZE="${max_heap_size_in_mb}M"
```

- Line 149

```bash
echo "Maximum memory allocation pool = ${MAX_HEAP_SIZE}MB, initial memory allocation pool = ${HEAP_NEWSIZE}MB"
```

After changing the Line 149:

```bash
echo "Maximum memory allocation pool = ${MAX_HEAP_SIZE}B, initial memory allocation pool = ${HEAP_NEWSIZE}B"
```

And the correct output in console is

```bash
---------------------
Starting IoTDB
---------------------
Maximum memory allocation pool = 4096MB, initial memory allocation pool = 800MB
...
```

title: FileNodeManager:  call the `Future#get()` returned from the merge thread
fix the future instance is replaced when the flush frequency is high
body:
If we call flush() twice (and in the 2nt calling, `value count` = 0), then the first future instance will be replaced. If there is exception in the first flush process, we will have no idea to catch it.

In this PR, we will wait to finish the last flush process before submitting a new one.

title: [IOTDB-67] call valueDecoder reset() when reading data from a new Page
body:
tsfile/example/src/main/java/org/apache/iotdb/tsfile/TsFileSequenceRead has a bug:

if the data type is Float and the TsFile uses RLE encoding, when we read data by using this class, an exception will occur if there are more than 2 pages in a chunk. 

It is because that for each page, we need to either call `valueDecoder.reset()` or generate a new decoder. However, the example java file does not.
